      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JETTER SON (1) was first up for a month when he drew very wide and raced parked but boxed on to place at this venue at his latest appearance. Has both a class drop and a much better barrier in his favour. That gives him strong claims. VINKE B NZ (5) drew wide and was held up in his latest attempt in the Autumn Gift final but did well to finish runner-up in a heat of that series prior. A repeat of that performance would stack up well in this line-up. Former WA pacer GREATGREAT BOULDER (10) came from a similar barrier to be beaten only 2.4m in his local debut. That was his first outing for two months so he should be better for it. SHADES OF MIKI (4) worked and faded in a good line-up at Bathurst last start but had been producing some decent efforts prior and is better off back to a distance where his record is good.",
